                <h4>Day 1: Basics and Stance</h4>
                <p>
                    <li>Stance and Balance Drill: Focus on your wicket-keeping stance and balance. Practice squatting down in a balanced position with your weight on the balls of your feet. Work on being ready to move in any direction.</li>
                    <li>Catching Practice: Have someone throw balls from different angles, focusing on catching techniques. Work on soft hands to receive the ball.</li>
                    <li>Footwork Drill: Work on quick and precise foot movements. Use cones or markers to simulate the movement of your feet while collecting the ball.</li>
                    
                
                
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card" id="card2">
            <div class="over">
                <h4>Day 2: Reaction Time and Glove Work</h4>
                <p>
                    <li>Reaction Drill: Use a tennis ball or reaction ball to improve your reflexes. Have someone bounce or throw the ball at you, and react quickly to catch it.</li>
                    <li>Glove Work: Practice catching balls with wicket-keeping gloves. Focus on the correct technique, ensuring that you're using the correct part of the gloves for different types of deliveries.</li>
                    
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card" id="card3">
            <div class="over">
                <h4>Day 3: Wicket-keeping to Spinners</h4>
                <p>
                    <li>Leg-spin and Off-spin Practice: Work with spin bowlers or use a bowling machine to practice wicket-keeping to spin deliveries. Focus on reading the spin and taking clean catches.</li>
                    <li>Stumping Practice: Work on your stumping technique. Have a spinner bowl from a distance, and practice collecting the ball and whipping the bails off quickly.</li>
                    
                </p><br>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div id="cards-container">
        <div class="card" id="card4">
            <div class="over">
                <h4>Day 4: Wicket-keeping to Pace Bowlers</h4>
                
                <p>
                    <li>Pace Bowling Practice: Practice wicket-keeping to fast bowlers, focusing on catching deliveries at different lengths and speeds.</li>
                    <li>Chest High Catch Drill: Have a fast bowler bowl chest-high deliveries, and work on taking catches cleanly and safely.</li>
                    
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card" id="card5">
            <div class="over">
                <h4>Day 5: Match Simulations and Communication</h4>
                <p>
                    <li>Match Simulation: Participate in match simulations or practice games. Focus on your communication with the bowlers and fielders, and practice directing the field placements</li>
                    <li>Calling Drill: Work on your calling while keeping wickets. Simulate run-out scenarios and practice making quick and accurate calls.</li>
                    
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card" id="card6">
            <div class="over">
                <h4>Day 6: Mental Toughness and Conditioning</h4>
                <p>
                    <li>Mental Toughness Training: Spend time visualizing different match scenarios and practicing your mental toughness as a wicket-keeper.</li>
                    <li>Fitness and Agility: Include fitness drills that improve your agility, speed, and endurance. Wicket-keepers need to be agile and quick on their feet.</li>
                    
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
